\begin{document}$$f(M_{i}) = \frac{1}{{1 + {\rm e}^{{ - a(M_{i} - M_{{i,t}})}} }}$$\end{document} The parameter “a” defines the steepness of the function, “Mi” is the concentration of the nutrient involved in the regulation of a flux and “Mi,t” is the nutrient concentration threshold.
